    public class Controller
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.awt.event.ActionListener, java.awt.event.MouseMotionListener, java.awt.event.MouseListener, java.awt.event.KeyListener
    Handles all direct interaction with the main window. Updates the game every time step.

    Ethan Parks

      • Controller

        public Controller​()
        Initialize all necessary classes for the game to run. Starts a thread to listen for user input on the command line.

    • Method Detail

      • control

        public void control​(java.lang.String mapFileLocation)
        Set this class as the listener for the view created in the constructor. Load map into the model. Start the timer for the update function.
        Parameters:
        mapFileLocation - Location of the map file to be read.

      • actionPerformed

        public void actionPerformed​(java.awt.event.ActionEvent e)
        Responds to button presses in the main window. If "Buy Tower" is clicked, the game begins the potential tower placement. if "Pause" is clicked, the game switches from paused to playing or vice versa.
